# Code Chunk Analysis of the Accordion Component

I'll break down the different sections of the Accordion component file and explain what each code chunk does:

## 1. Imports Section
```tsx
"use client";

import * as React from "react";
import { Collapsible } from "@base-ui-components/react/collapsible";
import styles from "./Accordion.module.css";
import "@/app/components/theme.css";
```

- `"use client"` directive: Tells Next.js this is a client-side component (will run in the browser)
- React import: Brings in React core functionality
- Collapsible import: Imports the base UI component that provides the collapse/expand functionality
- CSS modules import: Imports component-specific styles as a JavaScript object
- Global theme import: Imports shared theme styles

## 2. Type Definitions
```tsx
export type AccordionProps = {
    title: React.ReactNode;
    children: React.ReactNode;
    defaultOpen?: boolean;
    className?: string;
    onOpenChange?: (open: boolean) => void;
};
```

- TypeScript type definition that defines the props/parameters the component accepts:
  - `title`: The header content (can be text, component, etc.)
  - `children`: The collapsible content
  - `defaultOpen`: Boolean to control initial state (optional with default false)
  - `className`: For adding custom CSS classes (optional)
  - `onOpenChange`: Callback function when open state changes (optional)

## 3. Component Definition and Props Destructuring
```tsx
