    title,
    children,
    defaultOpen = false,
    className = "",
    onOpenChange,
    ...props
}: AccordionProps &
    Omit<React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>, keyof AccordionProps>) => {
```

- Defines the React functional component using arrow function syntax
- Destructures the props with default values
- Uses `...props` to collect any additional HTML attributes
- Complex type annotation:
  - `AccordionProps` (custom props we defined)
  - `&` (TypeScript intersection type)
  - `Omit<React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>, keyof AccordionProps>` (allows standard HTML div attributes while avoiding duplicates with our custom props)

## 4. State Management
```tsx
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = React.useState(defaultOpen);
```

- Uses React's useState hook to track if the accordion is open/closed
- Initializes with the value from the defaultOpen prop

## 5. Event Handler
```tsx
const handleOpenChange = (open: boolean) => {
    setIsOpen(open);
    if (onOpenChange) {
        onOpenChange(open);
    }
};
```

- Callback function that updates local state and calls any provided callback
- Updates internal state and then forwards the event to the parent component if needed

## 6. CSS Class Construction
```tsx
const accordionClasses = [styles.Collapsible, className]
    .filter(Boolean)
    .join(" ");
```

- Creates a string of CSS classes by combining the base style with any custom classes
- `filter(Boolean)` removes any falsy values (like empty strings)
- `join(" ")` combines all classes with spaces between them

