# Redundant CSS Analysis

Looking at the Accordion CSS, there are a few redundant or unnecessary styles:

## Redundant Background Colors
```css
.trigger {
    background-color: transparent;

    @media (hover: hover) {
        &:hover {
            background-color: transparent;
        }
    }

    &:active {
        background-color: transparent;
    }
}
```
The hover and active states set `background-color: transparent`, which is already the default value set on the trigger. Since they're not changing anything, these declarations are redundant.

## Unnecessary Specificity
