What would be a good replacement for --collapsible-panel-height?
# Replacing the `--collapsible-panel-height` Variable

The `--collapsible-panel-height` CSS variable is being used to control the height of the accordion panel when it's open. Since this variable doesn't appear to be defined anywhere, we should replace it with a more reliable approach. Here are some good alternatives:

## Option 1: Auto Height (Recommended)

The best approach for an accordion is to use `auto` height, which lets the content determine the necessary height:

```css
.panel {
    display: flex;
    height: auto; /* Replace var(--collapsible-panel-height) with auto */
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.25rem;
    transition: all 150ms ease-out;

    &[data-starting-style],
    &[data-ending-style] {
        height: 0;
    }
}
```

This allows the panel to grow based on its content and works well with the Collapsible component from base-ui, which handles the animation from collapsed to expanded state.

## Option 2: Max-Height Animation

Another common pattern for accordions is to use `max-height` instead of `height`:

```css
.panel {
    display: flex;
    max-height: 1000px; /* A value larger than any realistic content */
    height: auto;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.25rem;
    transition: all 150ms ease-out;

    &[data-starting-style],
    &[data-ending-style] {
        max-height: 0;
    }
}
```

This approach ensures that the animation works even with dynamic content sizes.

## Option 3: Define the Variable

If you want to keep using the CSS variable for consistency, you could define it in your theme.css file:

```css
:root {
    /* Other variables */
    --collapsible-panel-height: auto;
}
```

## Option 4: Dynamic Height Calculation with JavaScript

For the most precise animations, the Collapsible component from base-ui likely already has built-in mechanisms to calculate and animate heights properly.

In this case, you could remove the `height` property entirely from your CSS and let the component handle it:

```css
.panel {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.25rem;
    transition: all 150ms ease-out;

    &[data-starting-style],
    &[data-ending-style] {
        height: 0;
    }
}
```

## Recommended Solution

The best approach would be a combination of options 1 and 4:

```css
.panel {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.25rem;
    transition: all 150ms ease-out;

    /* These states are handled by the Collapsible component */
    &[data-starting-style],
    &[data-ending-style] {
        height: 0;
    }
}
```

This approach:
1. Removes the undefined CSS variable
2. Lets the Collapsible component handle height calculations and transitions
3. Maintains the transition effect
4. Works with any content size

This is the most maintainable solution that will handle content of any size while still providing smooth animations.

